
1. Consider a URL -> http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=HI-I6C0AAAAJ&hl=en
   - Create a connection -> con <- url("http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=HI-I6C0AAAAJ&hl=en")
   - Get the html ->  htmlCode <- readLines(con)
   - Close connection -> close(con)
   
   
2. Notes: Other packages:
  - httr 
    - Can be used for websites with user id, password. Allows you to pass these login credentials
    - Accessing APIs
  - XML
  - The concept of 'handle'. Get handle of the website and use it to access multiple times

3. Read Twitter API 
  - httr package
  - Create a Twitter App. Get consumer keys
  - Get tokens from Twitter
  - use 'oauth' functions to log in
  - use GET() # url can be obtained from twitter website
  - Use RJson package to read Json
  - Use jsonLite to convert json into data frame
